Program: Discovery
Title: Hydrates under the sea
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx5d
Last Broadcast Date: 17 June 1998
Hidden treasures under the sea, gas hydrates which form a solid under water. The material means that there could be huge carbon reserves under the sea. Also in the programme why the big drug companies are turning to nature with renewed enthusiasm for the medicines of tomorrow.